Gauteng hospitals are seeing a significant drop in new COVID-19 admissions. The province recorded the highest number of admissions mid-July. Acting Gauteng Health MEC Jacob Mamabolo discusses the situation with eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Acting Gauteng Health MEC Jacob Mamabolo says it is too early to celebrate the significant drop in COVID-19 admissions at Gauteng hospitals. "We cannot be complacent because the numbers have dropped, we must be on the alert, we must place the province on a high level of alertness. READ: COVID-19: Hospital admissions declining, says Mkhize "Globally we have seen the behaviour of the pandemic or virus, is that those countries that had initially celebrated victory, we are seeing that now they are going into renewed levels of lockdown," he said. The total number of confirmed cases in South Africa is 559,858. More than 400,000 patients have recovered from COVID-19. Watch the video above for more details. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.